        <h3 id="ideas">Top Environmental Actions</h3>
        <ul>
            <li class="idea">Reduce, Reuse, Recycle: Make it a daily habit!</li>
            <li class="idea">Plant Trees: They absorb CO2 and provide oxygen.</li>
            <li class="idea">Use Public Transport: Cut down on individual car emissions.</li>
            <li class="idea">Support Local: Buy from local farmers and businesses.</li>
            <li class="idea">Reduce Water Usage: Fix leaks and use water-saving fixtures.</li>
            <li class="idea">Switch to Renewable Energy: Opt for solar or wind power.</li>
            <li class="idea">Minimize Meat Consumption: Consider a plant-based diet.</li>
            <li class="idea">Volunteer for Clean-Ups: Participate in local environmental groups.</li>
            <li class="idea">Educate Others: Share knowledge about climate change and its impacts.</li>
            <li class="idea">Advocate for Policy Changes: Support legislation aimed at sustainability.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 id="questions">Common Questions About Climate Change</h3>
        <div class="question">
            <strong>What is climate change?</strong><br>
            Climate change refers to significant changes in global temperatures and weather patterns over time. While natural variations occur, human activities have accelerated these changes, leading to serious environmental impacts.
        </div>
        
        <div class="question">
            <strong>How can individuals make a difference?</strong><br>
            Individuals can help by reducing waste, conserving energy, supporting renewable energy initiatives, and advocating for environmentally friendly policies in their communities.
        </div>

        <div class="question">
            <strong>What are renewable energy sources?</strong><br>
            Renewable energy sources include solar, wind, hydroelectric, and geothermal energy. These sources are sustainable alternatives to fossil fuels and play a crucial role in reducing greenhouse gas emissions.
        </div>

        <h3 id="about">About This App</h3>
        <p>This educational app aims to raise awareness about environmental issues and encourage individuals to take action. It provides useful resources, practical ideas, and answers to common questions about climate change.</p>

        <h3 id="how-to">How You Can Help</h3>
        <p>You can contribute to a healthier planet by:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Implementing the ideas listed above in your daily life.</li>
            <li>Spreading awareness among your friends and family.</li>
            <li>Participating in local environmental events and initiatives.</li>  
            <li>Engaging with online communities focused on sustainability.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 id="thoughts">Final Thoughts</h3>
        <p>Every small action counts! Together, we can make a significant impact on our planet's health. Thank you for exploring Green Ideas!</p>

